Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.53,0:00:05.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're lucky everything \Nworked out for the best!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.87,0:00:08.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was reckless of you \Nto fly off like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.29,0:00:10.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.58,0:00:12.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As for the rest of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.12,0:00:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What would you have done if \Nsomething happened to your pilot?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.34,0:00:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.42,0:00:18.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They acted under my authorization.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.25,0:00:20.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, you've done well.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.97,0:00:23.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry back to the hospital \Nand get some rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.55,0:00:25.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.70,0:02:03.17,Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,"Your Hero"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.36,0:02:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing stands out as abnormal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.25,0:02:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're free to return to your own room.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.01,0:02:05.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But make sure to take it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.49,0:02:05.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.03,0:02:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, has Captain Suzukaze told you yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.56,0:02:09.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.66,0:02:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She wants me to reexamine \Nyou in two or three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.16,0:02:13.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More tests?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.23,0:02:14.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just to play it safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.50,0:02:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.11,0:02:21.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kei!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.42,0:02:23.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.59,0:02:25.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, yeah... Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.76,0:02:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something on my face?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.72,0:02:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've mellowed?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.95,0:02:33.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness! You're \Nback to your old self!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.69,0:02:35.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Officer Ange!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.69,0:02:43.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was her problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.82,0:02:45.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we head on back?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.20,0:02:47.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The doctor said I could \Nreturn to my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.99,0:02:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.13,0:02:59.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd you bring him to my room?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.39,0:03:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's just for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.00,0:03:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru, act all cool! Act cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.30,0:03:04.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.47,0:03:08.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, "I rock!" Say, "I rock!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.34,0:03:08.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.80,0:03:09.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say it while acting cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.40,0:03:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.18,0:03:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Quit messing with Izuru!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.18,0:03:19.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you go rest in your room?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.21,0:03:21.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's more relaxing \Nwhen I'm with everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.36,0:03:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go back once!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.91,0:03:32.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.28,0:03:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I wanted to offer \Na word of thanks...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.04,0:03:38.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much for saving me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.46,0:03:42.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should hold one after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.04,0:03:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ange needs a welcoming party!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.88,0:03:48.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A meeting between the GDF and \Nthe various economic powers?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.76,0:03:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. I will be accompanying the \NCommander in Chief to the meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.72,0:03:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't anyone tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.60,0:03:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.71,0:03:58.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I expect the AHSMB to be a \Nmajor topic on the agenda...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.37,0:04:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe they only informed \NCommander Simon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.11,0:04:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you switch to a private line?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.69,0:04:09.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. Just a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.82,0:04:11.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.70,0:04:14.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How much do you know \Nabout the AHSMB units?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.11,0:04:15.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In regard to...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.35,0:04:17.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The background behind their \Ntechnological origins.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.83,0:04:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the brilliant scientist Juria \NTsuda, who died at an early age,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.42,0:04:25.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,developed technology that \Nincorporated the pilot's DNA
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.68,0:04:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,into the central control system.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.53,0:04:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How was Juria able to \Ndevelop that technology?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.74,0:04:32.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know the specific details.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.80,0:04:36.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you don't know about how it \Ncame from a Wulgaru defector?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.10,0:04:38.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Wulgaru defector?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.93,0:04:40.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was such a person? Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.80,0:04:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he still alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.86,0:04:42.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The defector is still alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.94,0:04:46.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and currently under \Nthe MJP's custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.26,0:04:48.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why have you kept this a secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.28,0:04:50.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This person does not \Nwant an all-out war.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.28,0:04:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Out of the desire to save us,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.94,0:04:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this person has only offered \NWulgaru technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.32,0:04:57.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you sharing this with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.28,0:04:59.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Albeit unofficially, Commander Simon
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.78,0:05:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,has already released some \Nof this information.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.07,0:05:06.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't the AHSBM on the agenda \Nin this upcoming meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.51,0:05:07.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.64,0:05:10.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,only the Pacific Rim-Asia Alliance \Npossesses AHSMB technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.80,0:05:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I expect the other
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.34,0:05:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,economic powers to ask \Nfor AHSMB of their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.22,0:05:16.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.10,0:05:19.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The JURIA-System that \Nwe have installed on the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.39,0:05:20.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,AHSMB units is a dual-edged sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.23,0:05:23.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until the risks involved become clear,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.27,0:05:25.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we should postpone \Nsharing that technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.60,0:05:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.73,0:05:28.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll report in as soon \Nas the meeting is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.98,0:05:29.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.44,0:05:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this weighs heavy on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.88,0:05:33.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is this Wulgaru defector?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.03,0:05:36.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For now, I've said all I can...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.30,0:05:52.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.10,0:05:53.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}What gives?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.06,0:05:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}What are those GDF dudes doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.54,0:05:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This looks good!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.89,0:05:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamaki, did you invite them?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.09,0:05:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The more the merrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.59,0:06:00.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.82,0:06:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We just returned to Star Rose ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.49,0:06:06.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guiliano told us that you were
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.12,0:06:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,throwing a welcoming \Nparty for a new recruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.15,0:06:10.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Patrick was dying to come!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.40,0:06:12.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but Ange might be a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.90,0:06:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, actually, the one \NI wanted to see was...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.78,0:06:18.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ciao!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.95,0:06:21.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep! It's great that the world \Nis filled with all kinds of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.90,0:06:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got it wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.46,0:06:25.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.08,0:06:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Officer Ange, these are \Nour senior officers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.92,0:06:31.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're Team Doberman.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.71,0:06:33.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet ya, Ange.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.47,0:06:37.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The pleasure is all mine...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.68,0:06:44.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've improved a lot!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.12,0:06:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nah. I've still got a ways to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.85,0:06:48.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you still have a lot \Nof room for improvement?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.39,0:06:49.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's reassuring!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.94,0:06:52.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.22,0:06:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.90,0:06:55.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They need to reexamine you \Nin two days at the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.95,0:06:57.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just to play it safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.07,0:07:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't hurt to have \Nthem look you over, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.53,0:07:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.30,0:07:06.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Officer Ange, why don't you come closer?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.71,0:07:08.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This party is for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.79,0:07:09.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.95,0:07:11.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ange!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.13,0:07:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.96,0:07:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ange, why does your personality change
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.96,0:07:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when you pilot your AHSBM?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.51,0:07:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you realize that you act \Nlike a different person?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.30,0:07:22.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-you're wild and \Nbursting with energy...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.68,0:07:24.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're just like an AK-47.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.89,0:07:27.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're powerful, but unpredictable \Nwhen you cut loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.30,0:07:29.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you're tough, tenacious and simple,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.59,0:07:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}making your highly reliable and durable!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.03,0:07:32.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been meaning to ask \Nyou about this as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.31,0:07:34.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not really sure why \NI change personalities,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.90,0:07:38.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but when I get inside of my AHSMB, \Nit's like a different me surfaces...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.03,0:07:42.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard of people acting \Ndifferently when they drive,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.49,0:07:44.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's extreme in your case.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.30,0:07:46.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru acted a bit strange \Nlast time as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.85,0:07:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's because of how \Ndesperate the situation was?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.16,0:07:52.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But those situations seem to force \Nthe best results out of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.67,0:07:54.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were both incredible!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.80,0:07:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we've got two ace pilots, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.04,0:07:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ange, you were great!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.12,0:07:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So anyway-
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.70,0:08:02.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?\NDoes your stomach hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.66,0:08:04.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Suruga, shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.69,0:08:04.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A bunch of things hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.67,0:08:17.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.29,0:08:18.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? It's just you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.08,0:08:21.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't you act a bit \Nhappier to see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.57,0:08:22.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Out on errands?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.49,0:08:23.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Basically.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.74,0:08:26.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ordered some ice cream \Ncones, so go pay for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.54,0:08:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to pay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.38,0:08:33.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.96,0:08:35.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.80,0:08:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.33,0:08:42.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.05,0:08:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm willing to hear you out!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.90,0:08:45.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's none of your business.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.43,0:08:46.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She may have turned out down,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.97,0:08:49.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but time heals everything, \Nso you'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.69,0:08:50.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.85,0:08:52.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one turned me down!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.10,0:08:53.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what's your problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.98,0:08:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I realized that as a pilot, I'm \Nnothing compared to those two.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.57,0:09:01.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez! That's all this is about?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.16,0:09:05.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When did they get so far ahead of me...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.60,0:09:08.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asagi, you have plenty of good \Nqualities that are yours alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.60,0:09:11.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your face!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.83,0:09:14.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really are King Considerate!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.79,0:09:18.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hearing that from you doesn't \Nmake me the least bit happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.47,0:09:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And am I seriously turning \Nto a kid for moral support?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.80,0:09:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Officer Ange, you're fine.\N We'll handle the cleanup.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.44,0:09:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'll lend a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.60,0:09:31.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asagi left sometime during \Nthe party, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.43,0:09:34.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He might have gotten a tummy \Nache after eating too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.42,0:09:36.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we drop by his room later?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.81,0:09:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.53,0:09:42.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master Daneel! Did you come to see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.82,0:09:43.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only in your dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.99,0:09:47.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru, Daneel said that he'd \Nlike to have a word with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.28,0:09:49.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.33,0:09:51.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Teoria said that she
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.36,0:09:53.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,wishes to dine with you \Nif you are willing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.83,0:09:56.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For real?! As in a date?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.68,0:09:58.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a dinner meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.30,0:10:01.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then could I go with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.54,0:10:03.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master Daneel, aren't you coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.33,0:10:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although I will be nearby, \NI will not dine with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.22,0:10:08.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So they'll be alone? \NIt really is a date!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.82,0:10:11.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru's getting the jump on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.73,0:10:14.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.39,0:10:18.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope. He froze.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.69,0:10:24.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you choose me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.45,0:10:26.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're here on behalf of Simon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.66,0:10:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commander Simon isn't attending?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.05,0:10:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He isn't feeling well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.99,0:10:33.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw him just before \NI left to come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.50,0:10:34.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He seemed well enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.89,0:10:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are a variety of \Npolitical games at play.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.42,0:10:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's about to begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.25,0:10:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's begin the meeting!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.27,0:10:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.34,0:10:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.70,0:10:47.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Izuru Date Battle Plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.11,0:10:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Date...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.93,0:10:49.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't they just going out to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.55,0:10:52.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right! He'll be alone \Nwith his dream girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.49,0:10:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alone with her...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.10,0:10:57.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It might be a good idea \Nto loosen up a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.06,0:11:00.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roll your shoulders! Roll your neck!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.42,0:11:01.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.73,0:11:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Izuru! Love \Nis a game of politics!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.78,0:11:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've gotta check out the girl's \Nspecs, imagine all possible scenarios,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.42,0:11:09.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,devise a counter for each one \Nand pick a plan of attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.44,0:11:12.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ultimately, you gotta aim for \Nher heart and hit it dead on!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.52,0:11:14.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Love struck!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.87,0:11:16.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since the Battle of Ceres,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.34,0:11:18.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Wulgaru have gradually \Nbeen pushing the GDF back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.17,0:11:21.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this war continues,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.04,0:11:24.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all we will do is lose \Nmore lives and money.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.26,0:11:27.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We would hold peaceful \Nnegotiations if we could.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.38,0:11:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly! Our only option is to \Nfight back with all we have.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.30,0:11:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We intend to increase our \Nbudget for defenses by 30%.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.22,0:11:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We hope to help however we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.18,0:11:36.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The same is true of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.56,0:11:39.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To meet those ends, we would like \Nyou to share your AHSMB technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.81,0:11:42.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, the MJP's \Ncommander was unable
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.43,0:11:45.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to attend this meeting \Ndue to health problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.03,0:11:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only way to fight on \Npar with the Wulgaru is to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.11,0:11:50.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,bolster the AHSMB team \Nwith all due haste!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.42,0:11:52.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We lack the time required \Nto train new pilots.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.83,0:11:54.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We would train them ourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.77,0:11:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The AHSMB are still prototypes, \Nso how about the Rhinos instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.66,0:11:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that the previous \Ngeneration model?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.71,0:12:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but the Rhinos are already \Nin line for mass production.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.34,0:12:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Veteran pilots could rival our pilots \Nwithin a short period of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.34,0:12:09.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They can be used immediately
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.15,0:12:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and are not as costly \Nas the AHSMB units.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.26,0:12:14.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They will have to do. We'll take them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.68,0:12:17.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's prepare to enter \Nnegotiations straightaway.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.68,0:12:20.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You satisfied the other \Nnations without handing
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.10,0:12:22.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,them the latest technology, and \Nstill managed to draw a profit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.88,0:12:26.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now do you see the precocious \Nposition I am in?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.07,0:12:28.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I may lead the GDF,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.39,0:12:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I am also the Minister \Nof the Ministry of Defense
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.74,0:12:32.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for the Pacific Rim-Asia Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.66,0:12:34.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Chinese and African economic powers
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.57,0:12:37.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are lagging behind in space technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.15,0:12:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They hope to do well in this
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.84,0:12:41.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,war so they can acquire \Nnew rights in outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.71,0:12:44.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the time for \Nsuch petty politics?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.17,0:12:45.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't hand them everything
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.44,0:12:48.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and form massive AHSMB fleets \Nto oppose the enemy...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.03,0:12:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Assuming that was enough \Nto defeat the Wulgaru,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.00,0:12:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what would be left when we won?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.63,0:12:54.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We would lose our standing \Nas the world reproached us
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.35,0:12:56.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for using genetically altered \Nchildren in the war!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.06,0:12:58.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But only after they've \Nstolen our technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.85,0:13:03.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Somehow Bela-Russia has obtained \Nthe MJP's top-secret materials
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.91,0:13:05.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and is currently producing \Nmock AHSMB units.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.12,0:13:09.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone is only concerned with \Nclaiming rights over the resources in space, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.57,0:13:10.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The United Organization of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.93,0:13:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,American States is preparing \Nto present a battleship.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.85,0:13:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. They plan on \Nselling it during this meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.82,0:13:19.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like they don't care \Nto lose money or personnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.29,0:13:22.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel horrible for those children.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.67,0:13:26.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're using them as chips in a \Npolitical game so we can stay in control!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.09,0:13:30.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, whether your \Ndate is a flop or not, Izuru,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.21,0:13:33.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,rests on whether you have \Ncontrol of the situation!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.34,0:13:34.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.64,0:13:36.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show a bit more interest!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.39,0:13:38.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let her boss you around!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.26,0:13:40.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've gotta make her \Nmarch to the pace you set.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.14,0:13:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Izuru capable of doing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.59,0:13:44.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We wouldn't be holding this \Nmeeting if I thought he could!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.25,0:13:49.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. This is my first time \Nhaving dinner alone with a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.84,0:13:51.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if we looked into \Neach other's eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.83,0:13:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,couldn't we see into \Neach other's hearts?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.61,0:13:56.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Wouldn't you wind \Nup eating in silence?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.66,0:13:58.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine with that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.16,0:13:59.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's unacceptable!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.02,0:14:01.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You two ladies!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.09,0:14:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give Izuru some ideas on \Nhow to make a girl happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.05,0:14:04.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.67,0:14:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're up, Tamaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.51,0:14:08.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd make me happy if he \Nfed me pickled fish guts!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.63,0:14:10.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that only holds \Ntrue for you, Tamaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.80,0:14:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how about you, Kei?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.92,0:14:12.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.42,0:14:17.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like it if he seemed \Nto enjoy the cake I baked.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.39,0:14:19.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pickled fish guts and home-made cake...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.25,0:14:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't take notes!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.91,0:14:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it'd be awesome if he \Nput on this cool expression
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.17,0:14:25.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while listening to me talk and \Ncomplimented a whole bunch!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.93,0:14:26.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"You're right, Tamaki."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.98,0:14:27.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"You're adorable, Tamaki."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.99,0:14:28.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.85,0:14:30.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like it if he did little things
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.60,0:14:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to show he cared and \Ntreated me kindly...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.99,0:14:35.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't turn Izuru into your ideal guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.68,0:14:36.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll do my best!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.99,0:14:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Act cool while listening \Nand complimenting her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.64,0:14:40.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And be kind while doing little \Nthings to show I care...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.78,0:14:43.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dude, if you try to do all \Nof that, you'll explode.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.87,0:14:46.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.06,0:14:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where've you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.79,0:14:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't come in my room \Nwithout permission!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.92,0:14:52.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have impeccable timing, Asagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.96,0:14:55.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, accompany Izuru on his date.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.30,0:14:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why should I?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.47,0:14:59.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That may be the best suggestion \NI've heard so far!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.26,0:15:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd feel better if I had \Nyou there with me, Asagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.47,0:15:03.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that might be a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.22,0:15:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they're alone, Izuru \Nmight start to tense up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.94,0:15:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I wouldn't have to worry \Nif it was the three of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.94,0:15:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asagi, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.65,0:15:18.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it time for your big date?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.57,0:15:22.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asagi, Izuru! Commander \NSimon wants to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.04,0:15:27.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did well in your last battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.16,0:15:28.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.54,0:15:30.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru Hitachi, how are you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.96,0:15:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that you underwent some exams.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.71,0:15:35.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, it's nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.76,0:15:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was told that I would need \Na reexamination, but I'm fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.30,0:15:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toshikazu Asagi, how about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.67,0:15:42.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... am fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.27,0:15:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Regarding your futures.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.23,0:15:49.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have the option to leave
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.00,0:15:51.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the battlefield and accept \Npositions as instructors.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.73,0:15:55.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, does this mean \Nyou are done with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.57,0:16:00.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to serve as an AHSMB pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.32,0:16:01.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.45,0:16:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only reason I'm even \Ngetting to dine with Teoria
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.97,0:16:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is because I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.36,0:16:09.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.57,0:16:11.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I have not been \Ndisqualified as a pilot,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.88,0:16:14.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would like to continue \Npiloting my AHSMB unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.34,0:16:17.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is what I have been trained to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.46,0:16:19.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot fathom a \Ndifferent path in life,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.72,0:16:21.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at least not right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.09,0:16:23.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.43,0:16:26.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am, why did the commander ask that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.39,0:16:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.18,0:16:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't think about \Nanything but that date, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.81,0:16:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To be young!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.85,0:16:33.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I have to get ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.11,0:16:36.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, do you have a minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.33,0:16:39.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.53,0:16:41.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I imagine the commander must
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.58,0:16:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,have been worried about Izuru's health,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.58,0:16:44.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but in my case...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.63,0:16:46.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did he ask about reassigning me
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.68,0:16:49.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because I'm unfit to serve as a pilot?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.71,0:16:51.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.12,0:16:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have the lowest Harmonic Levels...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.67,0:16:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And even as a pilot, compared \Nto Izuru and Ange...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.58,0:17:00.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The "Fail 5".
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.21,0:17:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that what you were \Ncalled back at the academy?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.54,0:17:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You had the aptitude,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.31,0:17:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but for some reason, none of you \Ncould live to your potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.95,0:17:09.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.68,0:17:12.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your major flaw is how you \Nworry about everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.77,0:17:15.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that is also your strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.36,0:17:20.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your assignment is to evaluate \Nyourself and then surpass yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.44,0:17:22.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.32,0:17:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great timing!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.11,0:17:24.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.07,0:17:27.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our mission is finally about to begin!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.79,0:17:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're bringing Asagi along?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.12,0:17:35.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's my escort! Teoria \Ngets to bring Daneel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.25,0:17:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I plan on waiting outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.63,0:17:38.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're almost there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.34,0:17:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where will they be eating?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.67,0:17:44.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At a restaurant that Teoria picked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.02,0:17:45.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if it's a fancy restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.26,0:17:49.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you hold the knife in your \Nright hand or your left?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.72,0:17:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.00,0:17:52.00,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,RED COMET\NOkonomiyaki Teppanyaki Grill
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.00,0:17:53.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OKONOMIYAKI
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.02,0:17:55.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.40,0:17:58.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is a private room in the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.69,0:18:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.11,0:18:07.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru, I'm glad you could make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.33,0:18:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please take a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.49,0:18:10.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.62,0:18:13.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall be waiting outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.62,0:18:15.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you need me for anything, \Nplease call for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.58,0:18:16.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Same here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.89,0:18:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Asagi, if you like, you're \Nwelcome to join us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.26,0:18:24.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Wulgaru army is approaching the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.88,0:18:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,perimeter of our absolute defense zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.75,0:18:29.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They will clash with \Nour army in 30 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.23,0:18:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't create a pause in the bombardment!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.80,0:18:39.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care if the barrels burn out!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.94,0:18:43.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who falls so much as a step \Nback will be shot on the spot!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.25,0:18:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure that we're constantly in \Nfront of the Bela-Russian fleet!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.32,0:18:47.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All ships, take off!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.03,0:18:49.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show the Great Chinese Alliance
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.92,0:18:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that Bela-Russia has \Ndeveloped its own fighters!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.55,0:19:07.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one ever mentioned going \Nup against this massive army!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.29,0:19:10.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have the Great Chinese \NAlliance, Bela-Russia
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.88,0:19:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the MJP's allied forces on our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.44,0:19:15.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They probably aren't \Nrelaying their information.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.88,0:19:17.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you be so calm?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.17,0:19:19.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't win if we can't work together!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.75,0:19:22.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The MJP's reinforcements \Nshould be here momentarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.65,0:19:24.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll all work out if we \Ncan survive that long.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.97,0:19:26.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn! I can't ask the bunnies
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.77,0:19:28.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to save our sorry hides all of the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.11,0:19:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! This time, I'm \Ngoing to protect Tamaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.18,0:19:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Patrick, you look kinda different.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.08,0:19:36.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"You judge a man by his looks"!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.50,0:19:38.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Randy, you're the one \Nwho always says that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.59,0:19:46.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are your preparations \Nproceeding, Lumes?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.42,0:19:47.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.17,0:19:52.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you could draw the Earthlings' \Nattention for a while longer,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.01,0:19:54.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we should be able to slip through \Ntheir defenses with ease.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.47,0:19:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.48,0:19:58.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A squad is approaching from behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.35,0:20:02.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could they have perceived \Nwhat our ulterior motive is?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.23,0:20:03.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.94,0:20:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Klein!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.83,0:20:15.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you find this kind \Nof restaurant agreeable?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.45,0:20:16.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.62,0:20:19.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had Daneel look for one where \Nyou would feel comfortable
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.01,0:20:20.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so you wouldn't tense up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.59,0:20:23.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Daanel picked this place out?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.53,0:20:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Daneel".
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.66,0:20:25.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.13,0:20:30.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Supposedly your manager \Nrecommended this restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.38,0:20:32.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,R-really?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.89,0:20:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's about time I flipped this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.90,0:20:43.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.11,0:20:44.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it'll still taste the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.69,0:20:45.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.48,0:20:47.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a rather unique dish, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.32,0:20:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not really. I just messed it up...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.79,0:20:52.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What goes in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.62,0:20:55.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vegetables, wheat and... \Na bunch of stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.49,0:20:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.88,0:20:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am always impressed by \Nyour culinary culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.87,0:21:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Impressed?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.87,0:21:03.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did I use the word incorrectly?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.71,0:21:05.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you used it correctly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.75,0:21:08.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was something I had never considered.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.30,0:21:11.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Earthlings are a race \Nrich in culture and you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.51,0:21:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,possess various emotions referred \Nto collectively as your "heart".
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.18,0:21:17.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came with the intent to save you,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.57,0:21:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,yet I have learned so \Nmuch in the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.77,0:21:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am most grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.31,0:21:22.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Same here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.46,0:21:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm only here because \Nyou came to our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.48,0:21:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I also learned the concept of \N"gratitude" after coming here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.03,0:21:32.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The same goes for taking others into \Nconsideration and worrying about others.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.28,0:21:36.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In Wulgaru, everyone is only interested \Nin their own desires and lusts.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.45,0:21:41.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I am filled with the wish \Nto protect you and your kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.41,0:21:46.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Teoria, I-I want to protect you, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.41,0:21:47.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.45,0:21:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cool them down!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.84,0:21:51.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.05,0:21:52.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.88,0:21:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had you come here today
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.24,0:21:56.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because I am concerned about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.81,0:21:58.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You see...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.60,0:22:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to interrupt your meal!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.43,0:22:04.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've been ordered to sortie!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.69,0:22:08.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Wulgaru army has broken \Npast our absolute defense zone!
